cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.HC. 

This paper focuses on the awareness and experience of developers with outdated and license-violating code on Stack Overflow, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper touches on issues related to copyright (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it discusses the behavior of both answerers and visitors on Stack Overflow. Finally, the paper also mentions licensing conflicts (cs.CY) between the copied Stack Overflow code and the user's software.
